fields.name: Niall Burke
fields.description: Having only competed in the inaugural FIFA Tournament, Burke failed to showcase his raw talent on the biggest stage. A confident and competent competitor, Burke will hope to shake up the competition on his return to action this year.

fields.name: Lyes Djennadi
fields.description: Lyes proved last year that he could compete with the best, achieving a number of results by frustrating some of the bigger players. His form dipped following his hiatus during the middle of the tournament, resulting in him appearing in the last playoff yet again. Will improved focus lead to improved FIFA for Lyes?

fields.name: Jim Fogarty
fields.description: There is little known about Jim as a FIFA competitor. Having only competed in one FIFA Tournament to date, he looks like a middle of the pack player, but don’t be shocked if he pulls off a few surprises this year.

fields.name: Kunal Kapoor
fields.description: An ever-present in the FIFA Tournament, Kunal has consistently finished in the top half but has proven himself to be a bit erratic when it comes to his results. The inaugural champion, Kunal could be a dark horse for this year’s competition.

fields.name: Fabian Mak
fields.description: Fabian has shown his attacking flare and resolute defending in past tournaments. He is expected to navigate through the league stage easily but will the pressure of the knockout stages get to him once again?

fields.name: Cameron McBain
fields.description: An unknown quantity, Cameron McBain was brought in as a last minute replacement for tournament favourite, Robert McDaid. This is Cameron’s first appearance in the FIFA Tournament. He’ll be looking to impress in his debut.

fields.name: Johnny McNulty
fields.description: The 2017 champion, Johnny failed to return to defend his title as he did not compete in the 2018 FIFA Tournament. Returning to action after a year-long absence, he will be looking to reclaim the trophy from Peter O’Donnell.

fields.name: Peter O'Donnell
fields.description: Defending Champion Peter was the fairy tale story from the 2018 FIFA Tournament, defying all odds after a 4th place finish in the league. A tactically astute competitor, expect Peter not to give up his title without a fight.

fields.name: Daniel Whitaker
fields.description: A world-renowned pundit, Daniel has failed to get his tactics right in the FIFA Tournament yet. Boasting a defensive style of play, Daniel has been known to frustrate his opponents at times but has made a habit of finishing lower in the table. Will he make the necessary adjustments this year to improve?
